```graphql
type Query {
  user(id: ID!): User
  users(limit: Int = 10): [User!]!
}

query GetUser($id: ID!) {
  user(id: $id) { name email }
}
```
**Query** is the read-only entry point. Variables prefixed with `$` are passed separately.

```graphql
mutation CreateUser($input: CreateUserInput!) {
  createUser(input: $input) {
    id
    name
  }
}
```
**Mutation** modifies server data. Use input types for complex arguments.

```graphql
type Subscription {
  messageAdded(channelId: ID!): Message!
  userStatusChanged: UserStatus!
}

subscription OnMessage($channelId: ID!) {
  messageAdded(channelId: $channelId) {
    text
    sender { name }
  }
}
```
**Subscription** receives real-time updates via WebSocket. Server pushes data when events occur.

```graphql
fragment UserFields on User {
  id
  name
  email
}

query {
  user(id: "1") { ...UserFields }
  admin: user(id: "2") { ...UserFields }
}
```
**fragment** avoids field duplication. Spread with `...FragmentName`.

```graphql
input CreateUserInput {
  name: String!
  email: String!
  role: Role = USER
}

mutation {
  createUser(input: { name: "John", email: "j@e.com" }) { id }
}
```
**input** types are used for mutation arguments. Can only contain scalars, enums, and other input types.

```graphql
interface Node {
  id: ID!
}

type User implements Node {
  id: ID!
  name: String!
}

type Post implements Node {
  id: ID!
  title: String!
}
```
**interface** defines shared fields. Types that implement an interface must include all its fields.

```graphql
union SearchResult = User | Post | Comment

query {
  search(term: "hello") {
    ... on User { name }
    ... on Post { title }
    ... on Comment { text }
  }
}
```
**union** represents one of several types. Use inline fragments `... on Type` to select fields.

```graphql
enum Role {
  ADMIN
  USER
  MODERATOR
}

enum SortOrder {
  ASC
  DESC
}
```
**enum** defines a set of allowed values. Enums are serialized as strings.

```graphql
extend type Query {
  posts: [Post!]!
}

extend type User {
  posts: [Post!]!
}
```
**extend** adds fields to an existing type. Useful for modular schema design and federation.

```graphql
interface Timestamped {
  createdAt: DateTime!
  updatedAt: DateTime!
}

type Post implements Node & Timestamped {
  id: ID!
  createdAt: DateTime!
  updatedAt: DateTime!
}
```
**implements** declares that a type fulfills one or more interfaces. Use `&` for multiple.

```graphql
query GetUser($id: ID!, $includeEmail: Boolean = false) {
  user(id: $id) {
    name
    email @include(if: $includeEmail)
  }
}

# Variables: { "id": "123", "includeEmail": true }
```
**Variables** pass dynamic values. Declared with `$name: Type` in the operation, passed as JSON.

```graphql
query {
  admin: user(id: "1") { name }
  viewer: user(id: "2") { name }
}
```
**Aliases** rename result fields. Required when querying the same field with different arguments.

```graphql
query {
  node(id: "123") {
    id
    ... on User { name email }
    ... on Post { title body }
  }
}
```
**Inline fragments** `... on Type` select fields based on the concrete type. Used with unions and interfaces.

```graphql
query GetUser($skipEmail: Boolean!) {
  user(id: "1") {
    name
    email @skip(if: $skipEmail)
  }
}
```
**@skip** excludes a field when the condition is true. Opposite of `@include`.

```graphql
query GetUser($withPosts: Boolean!) {
  user(id: "1") {
    name
    posts @include(if: $withPosts) { title }
  }
}
```
**@include** includes a field only when the condition is true.

```graphql
type Query {
  users(first: Int, after: String): UserConnection!
}

type UserConnection {
  edges: [UserEdge!]!
  pageInfo: PageInfo!
}

type UserEdge {
  node: User!
  cursor: String!
}

type PageInfo {
  hasNextPage: Boolean!
  endCursor: String
}
```
**Relay-style pagination** uses connections, edges, and cursors. The standard pattern for paginated queries.

```graphql
query {
  __schema {
    types { name kind }
  }
  __type(name: "User") {
    fields { name type { name } }
  }
}
```
**Introspection** queries the schema itself. `__schema` returns all types, `__type` returns details of one type.

```javascript
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    user: (parent, args, context) => {
      return context.db.users.findById(args.id);
    }
  },
  User: {
    posts: (user, args, context) => {
      return context.db.posts.findByUserId(user.id);
    }
  }
}
```
**Resolvers** are functions that fetch data for each field. Signature: `(parent, args, context, info)`.

```javascript
const server = new ApolloServer({
  typeDefs,
  resolvers,
  context: ({ req }) => ({
    user: getUser(req.headers.authorization),
    db: database
  })
});
```
**Context** is shared across all resolvers in a request. Use for auth, database connections, and data loaders.

```javascript
const userLoader = new DataLoader(async (ids) => {
  const users = await db.users.findByIds(ids);
  return ids.map(id => users.find(u => u.id === id));
});

// In resolver:
user: (parent) => userLoader.load(parent.userId)
```
**DataLoader** batches and caches database requests to solve the N+1 query problem.

```graphql
query GetUserProfile {
  user(id: "1") { name }
}

mutation UpdateUser {
  updateUser(id: "1", name: "John") { id }
}
```
**Operation names** identify queries in logs and dev tools. Required when a document has multiple operations.

```graphql
# Service A
type User @key(fields: "id") {
  id: ID!
  name: String!
}

# Service B
extend type User @key(fields: "id") {
  id: ID! @external
  orders: [Order!]!
}
```
**Federation** splits a schema across multiple services. `@key` defines entity identifiers. Use Apollo Federation.

```graphql
type User {
  id: ID!
}

query {
  user(id: "abc123") { name }
}
```
**ID** is a unique identifier serialized as a String. Not meant for display. Arguments accepting IDs coerce strings and integers.

```graphql
type Post {
  viewCount: Int!
}
```
**Int** is a signed 32-bit integer. For larger values, use a custom scalar like `BigInt`.

```graphql
type Product {
  price: Float!
}
```
**Float** is a signed double-precision floating-point value.

```graphql
type Feature {
  enabled: Boolean!
}
```
**Boolean** represents `true` or `false`.

```graphql
input FilterInput {
  status: [Status!]
  tags: [String!]
  dateRange: DateRangeInput
}

query {
  posts(filter: { status: [PUBLISHED, DRAFT], tags: ["tech"] }) {
    title
  }
}
```
**Input with lists** allows passing arrays of values for filtering and batch operations.

```json
{
  "data": { "user": null },
  "errors": [
    {
      "message": "User not found",
      "path": ["user"],
      "extensions": { "code": "NOT_FOUND" }
    }
  ]
}
```
**Error responses** include both `data` and `errors`. Partial data is returned when possible. Use `extensions` for error codes.

```graphql
query BatchQuery {
  user1: user(id: "1") { name }
  user2: user(id: "2") { name }
  recentPosts: posts(limit: 5) { title }
}
```
**Batching** — Multiple queries in a single request reduces round trips. Aliases distinguish repeated fields.
